= \"text-block\">Add 500 \u03bcL of cold 70% ethanol to each tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258919,"guid":"2D631CCB0709446FA495B0D4689B03F3","previous_id":1258918,"previous_guid":"56FD04BDA8DE433D88F6F198EC237A4A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E61CFB752B9F414AB0B9C1A31A8F6567","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ethanol precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7C36B0E40C0B4B338B07A1CAF24D4029","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Invert the tube to mix. Make sure the pellet is dislodged from the bottom so that it is properly washed.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258920,"guid":"DC69C761489A4B33A00802DBE5F0D96C","previous_id":1258919,"previous_guid":"2D631CCB0709446FA495B0D4689B03F3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"00ECDC64264F46E4BA63B1F7C1E3B51C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ethanol precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7940A89985F9482E90DD14F0AF9D90C4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 16,000g for 10 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258921,"guid":"EB74FDBDBC1A449C8B4E08F76E34162E","previous_id":1258920,"previous_guid":"DC69C761489A4B33A00802DBE5F0D96C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BC9D794B2259491AB9C987F693766398","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ethanol precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A38925E52EC747F7BC59423EAB5ECCBD","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove liquid again with pipettor. Be careful to avoid pellet.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258922,"guid":"83FC03BFCA7647E7ADAACA239785D112","previous_id":1258921,"previous_guid":"EB74FDBDBC1A449C8B4E08F76E34162E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8E18BC22BF474DD6BD39B3CE1A589C21","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ethanol precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"84069AF473974101910A8B3ABE0E0FE4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place tubes with open lids in the UV hood. Let sit until ethanol has evaporated, but pellets are still damp. If the pellets become powdery, they are too dry. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258923,"guid":"30158B98A7CF4F5D9FBF33AF09C340AC","previous_id":1258922,"previous_guid":"83FC03BFCA7647E7ADAACA239785D112","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4D48413736ED4024B6AA38F65A0507AA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ethanol precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"479206C1411547988EBB1B529F4C76DF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend nucleic acid pellets:<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">RNA<\/span><span>: 50-100 \u03bcL of UltraPure water, pipette to mix. If pellets don\u2019t readily dissolve, incubate at 55\u00baC for 30-60 seconds, but avoid heating for too long as RNA may degrade.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">DNA<\/span><span>: 50-100 \u03bcL of low EDTA TE. Heat to 55\u00baC for 10 or more minutes to dissolve pellet.<\/span><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"C311D1CF6E3D4DAE8B2AEAB43AAC367B","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Recipe for low EDTA TE: 10 mM Tris\u00adHCl 0.1 mM EDTA For 50 ml: 500 \u03bcl 1 M Tris\u00adHCl (pH 8.0) autoclaved 10 \u03bcl 0.5 M EDTA (pH 8.0) autoclaved \u2192 to 50 ml with milliQ H2O \u2192 filter sterilize with 0.22 \u03bcm syringe filter TE is good for DNA storage, but EDTA inhibits PCR. So this low EDTA TE buffer is a good compromise for storing DNA for later PCR amplification. You can also just use EB (10 mM Tris\u00adHCl, pH 8 or 8.5).<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":"","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258925,"guid":"B791C2C0204811EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"41140AE38D9D4369B7D89385E0D2A590","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Prepare DEB"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8A772ACA71064C4C93BF615A23A70DAC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This is a <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">total nucleic acid <\/span><span>extraction protocol that provides the option of obtaining both RNA and DNA in separate aliquots, though it is <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">optimized for RNA<\/span><span>. We have a separate protocol optimized for DNA.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258930,"guid":"FA5A8320204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258909,"previous_guid":"70F1F187407D409C992BAB477BA1EE21","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CC32073B279C4E6E856ABEA3D20A9922","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4499D8D8C808422E931B2CF3AB274A44","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">To obtain DNA from the same lysates:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add 300 \u03bcL UltraPure Water to the original tubes, shake gently to mix.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258931,"guid":"FA5E2CA0204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258930,"previous_guid":"FA5A8320204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6CCAA9D4AC7149FC828005400821F99A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"44F11F7BA37447EC84FE23492D16E022","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add equal volume (of total volume) of phenol \/ chloroform (pH 8.0) to each original tube. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258932,"guid":"FA627261204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258931,"previous_guid":"FA5E2CA0204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CFCAEACF70A9408B93C1C5D1AB1BD691","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4CE5519B9137434CAFE2BC75FE0A0FA1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Gently shake a few times and then centrifuge at 14,000g for 1 minute.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258933,"guid":"FA66DF30204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258932,"previous_guid":"FA627261204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AF58902A322C43A480FD6BE9CA50FFDE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BB483271E3134086B3D698270AB959B2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove supernatant to fresh tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258934,"guid":"FA6AFDE0204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258933,"previous_guid":"FA66DF30204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"18F296BF39EF445BA31D7AE4F5AEBB96","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FBCFE940D0D3406DBE09C0CEB81C2838","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add equal volume of chloroform \/ isoamyl alcohol (24:1) to each tube. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258935,"guid":"FA6F1C90204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258934,"previous_guid":"FA6AFDE0204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9C3B55D2211E428BA6115BBEDA7F68BC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8463F5AA779340929E8E81BE99DAF0F8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Gently shake a few times and centrifuge. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258936,"guid":"FA73B070204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258935,"previous_guid":"FA6F1C90204911EC9C253D408FBABE86","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E5602FF570F441DBBFBB3C399973F8AA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Alkaline Phenol\/Chloroform Extraction"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"ED2B20E904CB4407A1F535758B7B4229","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove supernatant to fresh tube, carefully avoiding the bottom organic layer.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1258937,"guid":"EEC1A6A0204A11EC9C253D408FBABE86","previous_id":1258923,"previous_guid":"30158B98A7CF4F5D9FBF33AF09C340AC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FE86659F2DB64EACB0AADF61B0895B5A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ethanol precipitation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9026A6D20DC74277AEA227912F8CDDE1","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Convert <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">RNA<\/span><span> to cDNA immediately and store remaining RNA in -80\u00baC freezer. Once converted to cDNA, a working aliquot can be stored at 4\u00baC for short term purposes, or -20\u00baC or -80\u00baC for long term storage. Avoid repeated freezing and thawing of RNA and cDNA.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\">If RNA does not need to be converted to cDNA in the lab and is being prepped to be sent for RNA sequencing, quantify RNA and DNA present in RNA extract, and immediately continue on to concentrating\/cleaning bead step. Avoid freeze\/thaw cycles as RNA is highly unstable and will easily degrade.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\">DNA working aliquots can be stored at 4\u00baC. For long-term storage, place at -20 or -80\u00baC, but avoid repeated freezing and thawing of the DNA. One strategy is to keep half at 4\u00baC for the working sample and store the other half at -80\u00baC as the archive sample. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#E57785","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Modified 2020 by H. Lizethe Pendleton from the Brazelton Lab DNA extraction protocol.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1632826987}